# .github/CODEOWNERS
# BLUEPRINT: Composer 2 implements from this structure
# PURPOSE: Code ownership for review routing. Per spec §26.7 item 203.
# FORMAT: path-pattern → @team-or-user (GitHub login or team slug)
# SECTIONS:
#   - Default: all files require maintainer review
#   - queue/: queue maintainers (humans who manage work orchestration)
#   - .cursor/: platform maintainers (agents and humans who maintain the machine)
#   - docs/: documentation maintainers
#   - apps/api/: backend maintainers
#   - deploy/: infrastructure maintainers
# DESIGN DECISIONS:
#   - Placeholders use @{{ORG}}/{{TEAM}} format — filled during initialization
#   - Root * catch-all ensures no file is unowned
#   - Scoped ownership reduces review bottlenecks for specialized areas

# Default owners for everything
* @{{ORG}}/maintainers

# Queue system — humans who manage agent work orchestration
queue/ @{{ORG}}/queue-maintainers

# Machine control layer — platform maintainers
.cursor/ @{{ORG}}/platform-maintainers
AGENTS.md @{{ORG}}/platform-maintainers
spec/ @{{ORG}}/platform-maintainers

# Documentation — docs maintainers
docs/ @{{ORG}}/docs-maintainers

# API — backend maintainers
apps/api/ @{{ORG}}/backend-maintainers
packages/ @{{ORG}}/backend-maintainers

# Infrastructure — infra maintainers
deploy/ @{{ORG}}/infra-maintainers
.github/workflows/ @{{ORG}}/infra-maintainers
docker-compose.yml @{{ORG}}/infra-maintainers

# Security-sensitive files — security reviewers
.bandit.yml @{{ORG}}/security-reviewers
trivy.yaml @{{ORG}}/security-reviewers
docs/security/ @{{ORG}}/security-reviewers
